name: Astro Globes: The Pleiades
description:
Astro Globes is a series of uniquely processed astrophotography from my own collection with each image featuring a different object in our skies. 
The Pleiades, also known as M45 or the Seven Sisters, is an open start cluster and the nearest Messier object to Earth. The blue nebulosity is caused by galactic dust the makes this reflection nebula so magnificent.
